Title: Multiattribute One-Switch Utility
Abstract: The one-switch property states that the preference between any two lotteries switches at most once as wealth increases. Working within the expected utility framework, we extend the one-switch notion to the multiattribute case and identify the families of multiattribute utility functions that are one-switch. We then show that all multiattribute one-switch utility functions can be approximated by a sum of two multiattribute exponential utilities (sumex utility). Finally, we discuss how the one-switch property, when appropriate, can simplify the assessment of multiattribute utility. <i>This paper was accepted by Peter Wakker, decision analysis.</i>
Keywords: decision analysis, multiattribute utility, one-switch property, utility assessment, sumex utility
